Employer :  Advanced G.P.R Corporation
Posted On :  29/01/2021
Job Description :  Advanced G.P.R. corporation was founded by an American entrepreneur Kevin Pine with the intent to innovatively specialize in non-destructive testing when it comes to ground penetrating radar services and concrete scanning, which is consistently supporting ongoing industries within construction and essential to our community. Advanced G.P.R. is committed to the long process of exploring new methods in identifying the various unique and numerous materials, voids, and leaks at slab grade that X-Ray simply cannot do. Advanced G.P.R. offers Engineers a unique opportunity to show case their hard earned skills and have continual growth within their career all while being out in the field doing hands on work. Ready to join the Advanced G.P.R. team?

The Engineering Intern is responsible for supporting Advanced G.P.R.s Field Engineering team with participating in process improvement initiatives, completing on site projects and working on technical reports, as well as networking with other possible contractors on site. Youll gain direct, hands-on experience working with our Field Engineers and wont be stuck sitting at a desk.

We are seeking undergraduate students in the Phoenix/Scottsdale area (or returning to Phoenix/Scottsdale for the summer break) majoring in Mechanical Engineering, Civil Engineering, Construction Engineering, or Industrial Engineering with a passion for continuous personal growth.

Successful Engineers:

